#originalTopic=Debate:_Single-payer_universal_health_care
 The majority of doctors in the US support universal health care A 2008 survey of over 2,000 American doctors found that 59 percent support legislation to establish a national health insurance program, while 32 percent said they opposed it, researchers reported in the journal Annals of Internal Medicine[1]
